      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical) with documented QA procedures; version-controlled input decks stored in regulated document management system.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1 is a commercially validated solver subject to ISO 9001-compliant QA. Input decks are version-controlled under DePuy Synthes document control. Project requirements specify Gradation 2 minimum; achieved Gradation 3 through independent code-to-code verification against FDA in-house solver."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS suite reproduced within 1% for linear elastic beam bending and contact patch tests.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed against three NAFEMS benchmark cases. Maximum deviation 0.4%. Independent replication by FDA in-house solver confirms numerical correctness. Project requirements mandate Gradation 2; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <5% change in all three QoIs between medium and fine mesh densities.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on screw shank and bone block interface regions. QoI change between medium (1.2M elements) and fine (2.8M elements) meshes: stiffness 1.8%, yield force 2.3%, force at 40 mm 2.1%. All below 5% threshold. Discretization error estimated at 2.5% using Richardson extrapolation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance verified.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson convergence achieved at all 120 load increments with force residual norm below 1e-7. Energy balance confirmed within 0.1%. No spurious contact oscillations detected. Exceeds Gradation 1 project requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in original build; checklist-based review documented.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by independent senior analyst using a 47-item checklist covering boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application. Three minor issues identified and corrected prior to final simulation runs. Review documented in TR-2022-047."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear elastic-plastic material model with isotropic hardening; frictional contact (mu=0.3) at screw-bone interface; large-deformation kinematics enabled.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) consistent with published coupon data. UHMWPE bone block modeled as linear elastic (E=0.88 GPa). Frictional contact with Augmented Lagrange formulation. Large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) captures post-yield bending. Model form consistent with project requirements for nonlinear structural analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V coupon tensile tests (N=5) performed on same material lot as test constructs; mean and standard deviation reported. UHMWPE block properties from supplier certificate of conformance. Screw geometry from CMM measurements (N=3 screws); nominal CAD geometry used with measured tolerances as uncertainty bounds. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=500 runs)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lot; traceability to material certificates; tested across two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5) assembled from production-representative components with full material traceability. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; coefficient of variation <6% across QoIs. Sample size exceeds project requirement of N≥8."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate intended clinical loading envelope including at least two load magnitudes and two loading rates.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) and single load configuration per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition evaluated, which is below the project requirement of Gradation 3. This factor is flagged as below required level; risk is partially mitigated by the quasi-static nature of the clinical loading scenario and the conservative single-condition approach. Accepted with documented acknowledgment of limitation in the credibility argument."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen and fixture configuration.",
      "rationale": "One-to-one correspondence established between FEA model and each of the 11 test constructs using measured dimensions and lot-specific material properties. Fixture compliance measured and incorporated into boundary conditions. Equivalency documented in V&V Plan Rev C, Section 4.3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percentage difference <10%.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: E/uval=0.84, difference=3.2%. Yield force: E/uval=1.21, difference=5.7%. Force at 40 mm: E/uval=1.43, difference=6.9%. All metrics satisfy acceptance criteria. Uncertainty in validation metric accounts for both experimental measurement uncertainty and model input uncertainty via combined standard uncertainty formulation per ASME V&V 20."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory submission claims and failure modes of clinical interest.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the regulatory submission and directly address the clinical concern of screw-rod construct fatigue and fracture. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical and regulatory teams. Traceability to project requirements documented in requirements matrix RM-2022-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 compression-bending) is representative of the clinical use case; device geometry and material in validation match production design.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 is the accepted standard for spinal implant construct mechanical testing and is directly referenced in FDA guidance. Validation uses production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and rods. The compression-bending scenario is the governing failure mode for posterior spinal fixation constructs. Validation activity relevance confirmed by FDA reviewer correspondence (Q-submission Q200123)."
    }
