    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis that: (1) ASTM F1717 mandates a single standardized test condition, (2) the quasi-static clinical loading scenario is adequately represented by the single displacement rate, and (3) all quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference <10%) are satisfied across all three quantities of interest. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible for the intended regulatory submission supporting the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Project requirements are fully addressed in the credibility argument narrative and factor rationales.",
